# Critical Rules

## Generated API Clients - DO NOT EDIT

These directories contain auto-generated code that will be overwritten:
- `app/services/openapi/` - main API (openapi.yml)
- `app/services/chats/` - chats API (chats.openapi.yml)
- `app/services/channels/` - channels API (channels.openapi.yml)

Regenerate with: `npm run openapi:gen`, `npm run openapi:gen:chats`, `npm run openapi:gen:channels`

## TypeScript Strict Mode

- No `any` types - use `unknown` if type truly unknown
- No `as any` or `as unknown as <Type>` assertions
- All code must compile without errors
- Prefer `satisfies` over `as` for type narrowing

## i18n - No Hardcoded Strings

- All user-facing strings use translation keys from `app/i18n/en.ts`
- Use `useTranslation()` hook in components: `const { t } = useTranslation()`
- Use `translate()` function only outside components
- Use interpolation for variables: `t('key', { name: value })`

## Navigation

- Use typed navigation params, never `any` or unsafe casts
- Route params for IDs/primitives only
- Use `navigationFlowStore` for screen-to-screen callbacks
- Never pass functions in route params (not serializable)
